About Unchained Money                                                                                                                            
                                                                                                                                                 
  Unchained Money is your personal debt freedom roadmap. It analyses your income, expenses, loans, and savings to create a step-by-step plan to    
  become debt-free — using the avalanche method to save you maximum interest.
                                                                                                                                                   
  What it does:                                                                                                                                    
  
  - Financial Health Score — Calculates your score based on debt-to-income ratio and interest burden                                               
  - Month-by-month Roadmap — Shows exactly where every rupee of your surplus goes
  - Avalanche Method — Prioritises high-interest debt first to minimise total interest paid                                                        
  - Emergency Fund Building — Builds your safety net alongside debt payoff, with a medical buffer if you lack health insurance
  - Smart SIP Management — Pauses your SIP when high-interest debt exists (>10%) and resumes it automatically once cleared                         
  - Excess Savings Optimisation — Optionally uses savings above your emergency fund as a lump-sum payment to accelerate debt payoff
  - Progress Tracking — Motivational milestones as each loan gets cleared                                                                          
                                                                                                                                                   
  How it works — Examples:                                                                                                                         
                                                                                                                                                   
  Example 1: Ravi, salaried professional                                                                                                           
  Ravi earns ₹75,000/month, spends ₹35,000, and has two loans — a credit card outstanding of ₹2,45,000 at 42% and a personal loan of ₹4,10,000 at
  18%. Unchained Money identifies his surplus of ₹8,000/month, splits it 50/50 between emergency fund and debt, and directs all extra payments to  
  the 42% credit card first. When the credit card clears in month 14, its ₹8,000 EMI snowballs into the personal loan — clearing all debt by month
  28 instead of 42.                                                                                                                                
                                                            
  Example 2: Priya, freelancer with savings
  Priya has ₹3,00,000 in savings but only needs ₹1,20,000 for her emergency fund. She has a ₹2,00,000 personal loan at 16%. Unchained Money detects
   the ₹1,80,000 excess and offers a toggle — if she opts in, the excess is applied as a lump-sum, reducing her outstanding to just ₹20,000. Her   
  debt-free date moves from 22 months to 2 months.
                                                                                                                                                   
  Example 3: Ananya, no health insurance                    
  Ananya has no health insurance. Unchained Money adds a medical buffer (2 months extra) to her emergency fund target — raising it from ₹1,50,000
  to ₹2,50,000. Her roadmap accounts for the higher target, and the insurance warning explains exactly how much she can reduce her EF requirement  
  by getting ₹5,00,000+ cover.
                                                                                                                                                   
  Example 4: Karthik, SIP investor with debt                                                                                                       
  Karthik invests ₹10,000/month in SIPs but also has a ₹3,00,000 personal loan at 15%. Unchained Money pauses his SIP and redirects that ₹10,000
  toward the loan — because paying off 15% debt saves more than typical 10-12% market returns. Once the loan clears, his SIP resumes automatically 
  and his roadmap shows the exact month it restarts.        
                                                                                                                                                   
  What it doesn't do:                                                                                                                              
  - No financial advice — this is an educational planning tool only
  - No data leaves your device — everything is stored locally and encrypted                                                                        
  - No sign-up, no accounts, no tracking                                   
                                        
  Built for India — supports Indian currency formatting (lakhs/crores), local loan types (gold loans, LAP, informal lending), and accounts for PF,
  gold, and SIP in your financial picture.                                                                                                         
   
  Always consult a certified financial advisor before making major financial decisions.  
